# Local: start Postgres with `docker compose up -d`, then copy this file to `.env` and adjust if needed.
#
# Prisma 7: runtime queries use POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL (pooled in production). Migrations read POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING
# via `prisma.config.ts` (defaults to the same docker-compose URL if unset—see prisma.config.ts).
POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL="postgresql://chatter:chatter@localhost:5432/chatter"
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING="postgresql://chatter:chatter@localhost:5432/chatter"

# Production (Vercel): map Vercel Postgres integration URLs into these exact names:
# - POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL  ← pooled connection string
# - POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING ← direct (non-pooling) connection string
#
# After the first deploy, run migrations against the production DB (e.g. `pnpm db:deploy` locally with
# production env vars, or add `prisma migrate deploy` before `pnpm build` in the Vercel build command).

# NextAuth and OAuth (add your own values)
NEXTAUTH_URL=
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
GITHUB_ID=
GITHUB_SECRET=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
